    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1286"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1286">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the Council of People’s Commissars of the
                        Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stalin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="51" type="source" xml:id="d1286fn51">Copy of telegram obtained from the
                        Franklin D. Roosevelt Library, Hyde Park, N.Y. Notations indicate that this
                        message was received from Ambassador Gromyko at 4:15 p.m., and that a copy
                        was sent to the Department of State on the 29th with the President’s
                        statement, “no reply necessary”.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>I have received your message containing information regarding the issuance of
                    passports to Dr. Lange and priest Orlemansky. Although the Soviet transport is
                    considerably overloaded we shall provide Lange and Orlemansky with necessary
                    transport facilities. The Soviet Government is considering the trip of Lange and
                    Orlemansky to the Soviet Union as that of private citizens.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-28">March 28,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
